    (Note (NoteNumber 324)
        (NoteText "This must reference a valid Object instance.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 325)
        (NoteText "All the fields in the radio type struct are enumerations. The values for the individual fields (that do not use enumeration datatypes from within the RPR FOM) are to be derived from the federation agreements, which could refer to SISO-REF-010.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 326)
        (NoteText "This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (default value: 500m).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 327)
        (NoteText "At the time of publication of the Standard for RPR FOM 3.0, no IFF Data records have been defined for specific DAP data.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 328)
        (NoteText "IFF Data records have not been defined for specific DAP data. When such records are developed, it is recommended that the DAP field format from the appropriate ICAO publication be used.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 329)
        (NoteText "The size of this field in IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Section B.2.51 is assumed to be incorrect. According to ICAO documentation, this field in the extended squitter surface position BDS register is 7 bits, not 3. RPR FOM users should be careful in using the full range as per the ICAO specifications. For in heterogeneous exercises with DIS-based simulations this may lead to unexpected results. It is advised to explicitly note the allowed values and the mapping to be applied in gateways in federation/exercise agreements (when using Mode S squitter surface position reports).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 330)
        (NoteText "If there is no object instance associated with the attribute, then this should be set to the empty string (no characters). Refer to SISO-STD-001 Section 7.8.6 for handling empty strings.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 331)
        (NoteText "The update condition shall be evaluated as follows:The owner of a designator object shall maintain two state models of the object in support of the dead reckoning process. One model shall be the internal model used by the simulation application to represent that object. The other shall be a dead reckoning model of the object. Certain thresholds shall be established as criteria for determining if the object's actual spot location has varied by an allowable amount from the dead reckoned spot location. The attribute is updated when the object's actual spot location differs from the dead reckoned spot location by more than DRA_POS_THRSH (default value: 1 m).See IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Sections 4.6.6 and 5.3.2.3 and Annex E for more details.A TSPI update includes all attributes applicable to the dead reckoning algorithm. A TSPI update attribute may be omitted if its last updated value is within an established epsilon amount from its current value.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 332)
        (NoteText "This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (default value: 3 degrees).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 333)
        (NoteText "If emissions data is available (determined by the state of the EmissionsDataAvailable attribute) then this attribute shall be updated by the federate. If emissions data is not available then this attribute shall not be updated by the federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 334)
        (NoteText "This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (default value: 3 degrees).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 335)
        (NoteText "The EventIdentifier attribute is used to link together updates arising from a common event. For example an emitter function change can be linked to a frequency change in one of its associated emitter beams, by using the same event ID in the attribute updates to the appropriate EmitterSystem and EmitterBeam classes. It is important to note that in order that the EventIdentifier is delivered in the same reflect attribute values call in the receiving federates as the associated attributes, then all the attributes, including the EventIdentifier, must share the same transport type.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 336)
        (NoteText "The federate should change the value of the EventIdentifier when associating changes between two or more emitter beams and/or emitter systems. It is not necessary to update the EventIdentifier field with every attribute update if the change is not associated with changes in other instances of other classes.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 337)
        (NoteText "The epsilon value for the location is DRA_POS_EPSILSON (default value: 0.001 m), in any direction.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 338)
        (NoteText "The epsilon value for the linear acceleration is DRA_ACCEL_EPSILSON (default value: 0.001 m/(s^2)), in any direction.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 339)
        (NoteText "Frequency modulation shall be derived from database parameters stored for the particular emitting system and specified mode.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 340)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_FT_ESP_THRSH (default value: 10 m).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 341)
        (NoteText "For radar-like IFF interrogators, this may still be known as 'ERP' because EIRP is generally known throughout the radar community as ERP. The field is named \"ERP\" in IEEE Std 1278.1-2012, but it is believed that EIRP was the intended meaning.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 342)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_AD_PULRAT_THRSH (default value: 0.017 rad/s).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 343)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_AD_PULACC_THRSH (default value: 0.017 rad/(s^2)).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 344)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. For azimuth related data, the threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_AZ_THRSH (default value: 1 degree). For elevation related data, the threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_EL_THRSH (default value: 1 degree).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 345)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_FT_MWD_THRSH (default value: 10000 m).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 346)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_FT_KT_THRSH (default value: 10 s).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 347)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_FT_VEL_THRSH (default value: 1.0 m/s).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 348)
        (NoteText "Upon a value change, an update is only required to be published immediately when the change exceeds a threshold value. The threshold is defined by the symbolic name EE_FT_ACC_THRSH (default value: 1.0 m/(s^2)).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 349)
        (NoteText "If the IFF system is Mode 5 capable then this attribute shall be updated by the federate. If the IFF system is not Mode 5 capable then this attribute shall either not be published or set to False.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 350)
        (NoteText "The RRB system is a transponder only system.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 351)
        (NoteText "Special update conditions may apply to the datatypes or their fields used for the array elements. Refer to the datatype or field semantics, including any referenced notes, for more details.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 352)
        (NoteText "The object IDs in this structure shall refer to EmitterBeam objects (or subclasses of EmitterBeam).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 353)
        (NoteText "A change in sweep sync value alone does not require an update to be published. When one of the other beam attributes (center and sweep for azimuth and elevation ) requires an update publication, the sweep sync attribute shall be included when its value has changed since the last update.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 354)
        (NoteText "This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (default value: 1 degree).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 355)
        (NoteText "This must reference a valid Object instance.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 356)
        (NoteText "The object IDs in this structure shall refer to PhysicalEntity objects (or subclasses of PhysicalEntity).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 357)
        (NoteText "This attribute is updated if the current value differs from the previously updated value by more than the value specified by the symbolic name (default value: 1 degree).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 358)
        (NoteText "The term \"ERP\" is widely used throughout the radar community (including radar databases), but in radar contexts, the intended meaning is actually that of EIRP.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 359)
        (NoteText "If there is no object instance associated with the parameter, then this should be set to the empty string (no characters). Refer to SISO-STD-001 Section 7.8.6 for handling empty strings.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 360)
        (NoteText "Refer to SISO-STD-001 Section 7.13.1.1 for a detailed description of the update conditions of each of the alternatives possible as array element.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 361)
        (NoteText "This must reference a valid Object instance.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 362)
        (NoteText "This must reference a valid Object instance.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 363)
        (NoteText "The Acknowledge interaction is issued in response to the CreateEntity, RemoveEntity, StartResume, and StopFreeze interactions. See IEEE Std 1278.1-20128 Sections 5.6.5.6 and 7.5.6.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 364)
        (NoteText "The AcknowledgeR interaction is issued in response to the CreateEntityR, RemoveEntityR, StartResumeR, and StopFreezeR interactions. See IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Sections 5.12.4.6 and 7.11.6.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 365)
        (NoteText "The ActionResponse interaction should be sent in response to an ActionRequest interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 366)
        (NoteText "The ActionResponseR interaction should be sent in response to an ActionRequestR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 367)
        (NoteText "See IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Section 5.12 for a description of the acknowledgement protocols (called reliability services in that document).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 368)
        (NoteText "If the EntityNumber field is set to RQST_ASSIGN_ID (fixed value: FFFE (H)) then the receiving application should assign the entity number. Entity identifications shall be in accordance with IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Section 6.2.28")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 369)
        (NoteText "The Data interaction should be sent in response to a DataQuery interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 370)
        (NoteText "The DataR interaction should be sent in response to a DataQueryR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 371)
        (NoteText "The Data interaction should be sent in response to a SetData interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 372)
        (NoteText "The RemoveObjectResult interaction should be sent in response to an RemoveObjectRequest interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 373)
        (NoteText "The standard acknowledgement protocol is identical to the requirements of SIMAN in IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Section 5.6 (i.e. it acts identically to the parent interaction). The other acknowledgement protocols are described in IEEE Std 1278.1-2012 Section 5.12 (they are called reliability services in that document).")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 374)
        (NoteText "The ActionResponseFromObject interaction should be sent in response to an ActionRequestToObject interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 375)
        (NoteText "The AttributeChangeResult interaction should be sent in response to an AttributeChangeRequest interaction by any object that is mentioned in the associated object list. The AttributeChangeResult parameter should indicate the success or failure of the object to implement the requested changes. If the object can implement the changes then the AttributeChangeResult parameter should be set to successful and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty.If the object cannot immediately comply with the request, but is likely to be able to comply in the future then the AttributeChangeRequest parameter shall be set to pending and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty. When the object complies with the request (or fails to implement the request) then another AttributeChangeResult interaction shall be sent informing the initiating federate of the result of the request.If the object cannot comply with the request then the AttributeChangeResult parameter shall indicate the reason why the object cannot comply with the request. The AttributeValueSet shall contain the attributes which have been not been set and the current values of those attributes.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 376)
        (NoteText "The AttributeChangeResultR interaction should be sent in response to an AttributeChangeRequestR interaction by any object that is mentioned in the associated object list. The AttributeChangeResult parameter should indicate the success or failure of the object to implement the requested changes. If the object can implement the changes then the AttributeChangeResult parameter should be set to successful and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty.If the object cannot immediately comply with the request, but is likely to be able to comply in the future then the AttributeChangeRequest parameter shall be set to pending and the AttributeValueSet shall be empty. When the object complies with the request (or fails to implement the request) then another AttributeChangeResultR interaction shall be sent informing the initiating federate of the result of the request.If the object cannot comply with the request then the AttributeChangeResult parameter shall indicate the reason why the object cannot comply with the request. The AttributeValueSet shall contain the attributes which have been not been set and the current values of those attributes.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 377)
        (NoteText "The CreateObjectResult interaction should be sent in response to an CreateObjectRequest interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 378)
        (NoteText "The CreateObjectResultR interaction should be sent in response to an CreateObjectRequestR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 379)
        (NoteText "The ActionResponseFromObjectR interaction should be sent in response to an ActionRequestToObjectR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 380)
        (NoteText "The units of the FixedDatumValue field is determined by the value of the FixedDatumIdentifier field. The units, etc., for each of the FixedDatumIdentifier enumeration values are to be derived from the federation agreements, which could refer to SISO-REF-010.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 381)
        (NoteText "The type of the RecordStruct is determined by the value of the RecordSetIdentifier field. The types and associated units, etc., for each of the RecordSetIdentifier enumeration values The values for the individual fields are to be derived from the federation agreements, which could refer to SISO-REF-010.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 382)
        (NoteText "The DataR interaction should be sent in response to a SetDataR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 383)
        (NoteText "The RecordR interaction should be sent in response to a RecordQueryR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
    (Note (NoteNumber 384)
        (NoteText "The RecordR interaction should be sent in response to a SetRecordR interaction by the receiving federate.")
    )
)
